==Class Project Guidelines==
You may find this page helpful: [[Wikibooks:Guidelines_for_class_projects]]. It would also be good if you could encourage your students to create and log in to their own Wikibooks accounts rather than editing pages anonymously like recent edits to [[Data_Mining_Algorithms_In_R/Clustering]] & [[Data_Mining_Algorithms_In_R/Clustering/Density-Based_Clustering]]. Anonymous editing is a trick used by a small number of vandals who try to disrupt our work here, so the fewer anonymous edits occur the easier it is for the local counter-vandalism team to maintain the site. Anonymous editing also makes it difficult to credit contributions to particular authors, which you may need for assessing different individuals. Thanks [[User:Recent Runes|Recent Runes]] ([[User talk:Recent Runes|talk]]) 10:28, 17 December 2009 (UTC)

