{{ Cluster | | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 47 | image = [[image:M47a.jpg|280px]] | epoch = J2000.0 | class = II,3,m | ra = 07<sup>h</sup>&nbsp;36.6<sup>m</sup> | dec = -14° 30&prime; | dist_ly = 1.6 [[w:light year|kly]] | dist_pc = 490 Pc | appmag_v = 4.2 | size_v = 30.0&prime; | mass_kg = | mass_msol = | radius_ly = 6 | v_hb = - | age = 78 million years | notes = - | names = NGC 2422 }}
'''Open Cluster M47''' (also known as '''Messier Object 47''' or '''NGC 2422''') is an [[w:open cluster]] in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Puppis]]. It was discovered by [[w:Giovanni Batista Hodierna]] before [[w:1654]] and independently discovered by [[w:Charles Messier]] on [[w:February 19]], [[w:1771]].
M47 is at a distance of about 1,600 [[w:light-year]]s from [[w:Earth]] with an estimated age of about 78 million years. There are about 50 [[w:star]]s in this cluster, the brightest one being of [[w:apparent magnitude|magnitude]] +5.7.
==External links== * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m047.html Messier 47, SEDS Messier pages] * [http://www.waid-observatory.com/m047-2006-02-21.html Messier 47] Amateur Image - '' [http://www.waid-observatory.com Waid Observatory '']
