{{Infobox galaxy | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 49<ref name="jensenetal2003">{{cite journal | author=Jensen, Joseph B.; Tonry, John L.; Barris, Brian J.; Thompson, Rodger I.; Liu, Michael C.; Rieke, Marcia J.; Ajhar, Edward A.; Blakeslee, John P. | title=Measuring Distances and Probing the Unresolved Stellar Populations of Galaxies Using Infrared Surface Brightness Fluctuations | journal=Astrophysical Journal | month=February | year=2003 | volume=583 | issue=2 | pages=712–726 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2003ApJ...583..712J | doi=10.1086/345430 }}</ref> | image = [[image:M49a.jpg|250px|center]] | caption = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 49 | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | constellation name = [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]] | ra = {{RA|12|29|46.7}}<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 4472 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-09-26 }}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|+08|00|02}}<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 9.4<ref name="ned" /> | type = E2<ref name="ned" />, [[w:LINER]]<ref name="ned" /> |names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4472,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 7629,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 41220,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Atlas of Peculiar Galaxies|Arp]] 134<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''Messier 49''' (also known as ''M 49'' or ''NGC 4472'') is an [[w:elliptical galaxy|elliptical]] / [[w:lenticular galaxy]] about [[w:1 E22 m|49 million]] [[w:light-year]]s away in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]]. The galaxy was discovered by [[w:Charles Messier]] in [[w:1771]].<ref name="jones1991">{{cite book | author=K. G. Jones | year=1991 | title=Messier's Nebulae and Star Clusters | edition= 2nd | publisher=Cambridge University Press | location=Cambridge | isbn=0-521-37079-5 }}</ref>
==Supernovae== The only [[w:supernova]] observed within this galaxy is [[w:SN 1969Q]].<ref name="nedsupernovae">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for supernova search near name "NGC 4472" | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2007-02-12}}</ref> The supernova was discovered in June 1969.<ref name="barbonetal1984">{{cite journal | author= R. Barbon, E. Cappellaro, F. Ciatti, M. Turatto, C. T. Kowal | title=A revised supernova catalogue | journal=Astronomy & Astrophysics Supplement Series | year=1984 | volume=58 | pages=735–750 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1984A&AS...58..735B}}</ref>
==Companion galaxies== [[w:NGC 4467]] forms a visual pair with Messier 49{{Fact|date=February 2007}}.
==Virgo Cluster membership== Messier 49 is the brightest member of the [[w:Virgo Cluster]].<ref name="carnegieatlas">{{cite book | author=A. Sandage, J. Bedke | year=1994 | title=Carnegie Atlas of Galaxies | edition= | publisher=Carnegie Institution of Washington | location=Washington, D.C. | isbn=0-87279-667-1 }}</ref> The galaxy is located at the center of one of the subclusters within the Virgo Cluster.<ref name="carnegieatlas" />
==External links== * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m049.html SEDS: Elliptical Galaxy M49] * [http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/16456987/ Black hole found in a star cluster in M49]
