{{ Cluster | | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 50 | image = [[image:M50a.jpg|280px]] | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | class = II,3,m | ra = 07<sup>h</sup>&nbsp;03.2<sup>m</sup> | dec = &minus;08° 20&prime; | dist_ly = 3.2 [[w:lightyear|kly]] | dist_pc = 1 kpc | appmag_v = 5.9 | size_v = 16.0&prime; | mass_kg = | mass_msol = | radius_ly = 10 | v_hb = | age = 78 million years | notes = | names = NGC 2323 }}
'''Messier 50''' (also known as '''M 50''' or '''NGC 2323''') is an [[w:open cluster]] in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Monoceros]]. It was perhaps discovered by [[w:Giovanni Domenico Cassini|G. D. Cassini]] before [[w:1711]] and independently discovered by [[w:Charles Messier]] in [[w:1772]]. M50 is at a distance of about 3,000 [[w:light-year]]s away from [[w:Earth]]. It is described as a 'heart-shaped' figure.
