{{Infobox galaxy | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 59 | image = | caption = ''M59'', on [[w:Digitized Sky Survey|DSS2]], 0.1&deg; view. | credit = [[w:Palomar Observatory]]/[[w:STScI]]/[[w:WikiSky]] | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | constellation name = [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]]<ref name="sinnott1988">{{cite book | author=R. W. Sinnott, editor | title= The Complete New General Catalogue and Index Catalogue of Nebulae and Star Clusters by J. L. E. Dreyer | year=1988 | publisher=Sky Publishing Corporation and Cambridge University Press | isbn=0-933-34651-4}}</ref> | type = E5<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 4621 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-11-18 }}</ref> | ra = {{RA|12|42|02.3}}<ref name="ned" /> | dec = {{DEC|+11|38|49}}<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = [[w:1 E23 m|60 ± 5]] [[w:light-year|Mly]] (18.3 ± 1.7 [[w:parsec|Mpc]])<ref name="tonryetal2001">{{cite journal | author=J. L. Tonry, A. Dressler, J. P. Blakeslee, E. A. Ajhar, A. B. Fletcher, G. A. Luppino, M. R. Metzger, C. B. Moore | title=The SBF Survey of Galaxy Distances. IV. SBF Magnitudes, Colors, and Distances | journal=Astrophysical Journal | year=2001 | volume=546 | issue=2 | pages=681–693 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2001ApJ...546..681T | doi=10.1086/318301 }}</ref> | z = 410 ± 6 km/[[w:second|s]]<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 10.6<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 5&prime;.4 &times; 3&prime;.7<ref name="ned" /> | notes = | names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4621,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 7858, [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 42628<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''Messier 59''' (also known as ''M59'' or ''NGC 4621'') is an [[w:elliptical galaxy]] in the constellation [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]].
==History== Messier 59 and the nearby elliptical galaxy [[w:Messier 60]] were both discovered by [[w:Johann Gottfried Koehler]] in April [[w:1779]] during observations of a [[w:comet]] in the same part of the sky.<ref name="jonesbook1991">{{cite book | author=K. G. Jones | year=1991 | title=Messier's Nebulae and Star Clusters | edition= 2nd | publisher=Cambridge University Press | location=Cambridge | isbn=0-521-37079-5 }}</ref> [[w:Charles Messier]] listed both in the [[w:Messier Catalogue]] about three days after Koehler's discovery.<ref name="jonesbook1991" />
==Virgo Cluster membership== M59 is a member of the [[w:Virgo Cluster]].
==External links== * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m059.html Elliptical Galaxy M59 @ SEDS Messier pages]
