{{Infobox galaxy | name = [[w:Messier Catalogue|Messier]] 61<ref name="AnA">{{cite journal | last = Tschöke | first = D. | coauthors = Hensler, G.; Junkes, N | year = 2000 | month = August | title = X-rays from the barred galaxy NGC 4303 | journal = Astronomy and Astrophysics | volume = 360 | issue = 2 | pages = 447-456 | publisher = EDP Sciences | issn = 0004-6361 | url = http://arxiv.org/abs/astro-ph/0006361v1 }}</ref> | image = | caption = ''M61'', courtesy of [[w:NOAO]] | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | constellation name = [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]] | ra = {{RA|12|21|54.9}}<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for M 61 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-11-18 }}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|+04|28|25}}<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 10.18 | type = SAB(rs)bc<ref name="ned" />, [[w:Seyfert galaxy|H<sub>II</sub>Sy2]]<ref name="ned" /> | names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4303<ref name="ned" />, [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 07420<ref name="ned" />, [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 040001<ref name="ned" />, MCG +01-32-022<ref name="ned" />, USGC U490 NED310<ref name="ned" />, MRC 1219+047<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''[[w:Messier object|Messier]] 61''' (also known as ''M61'' or ''[[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4303'') is a [[w:spiral galaxy]] in the [[w:Virgo Cluster]]. It was discovered by [[w:Barnabus Oriani]] on [[w:May 5]], [[w:1779]].
M61 is one of the larger members of the Virgo Cluster.
Six [[w:supernova|supernovae]] have been observed in this galaxy: <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cfa.harvard.edu/iau/lists/Supernovae.html |title=List of Supernovae |accessdate=30 December 2008 |publisher=[[w:Central Bureau for Astronomical Telegrams]] }}</ref>
*SN 2008in *SN 2006ov *SN 1999gn *SN 1964F *SN 1961I *SN 1926A
[[image:SN2008inHunter Wilson.jpg|thumb|left|400px|Amateur Image of '''Messier 61''' Showing Supernova 2008in on April 16, 2009 Courtesy Hunter Wilson]]
