{{Infobox galaxy | name = Sunflower Galaxy | image = [[image:M63.jpg|250px]] | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | ra = {{RA|13|15|49.3}}<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 5055 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-10-10}}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|+42|01|45}}<ref name="ned" /> | type = SA(rs)bc<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = 37 [[w:Light year|Mly]]<ref>Frommert, Hartmut & Kronberg, Christine (2002). [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m063.html "Messier Object 63"]. Retrieved Dec. 26, 2006</ref> | z = 504 [[w:kilometer|km]]/[[w:second|s]]<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 9.3<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 12&prime;.6 &times; 7&prime;.2<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[w:Canes Venatici]] | names = [[w:Messier object|M]]63, NGC 5055, [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 8334, [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 46153<ref name="ned" /> }}
The '''Sunflower Galaxy''' (also known as ''Messier 63'', ''M63'', or ''NGC 5055'') is an [[w:unbarred spiral galaxy]] in the [[w:Canes Venatici]] [[w:constellation]]. It is a [[w:flocculent spiral galaxy]], consisting of a central disc surrounded by many short spiral arm segments. The Sunflower Galaxy is part of the [[w:M51 Group]], a group of galaxies that also includes the [[w:Whirlpool Galaxy|Whirlpool Galaxy (M51)]].
==History== The Sunflower Galaxy was discovered by [[w:Pierre Méchain]] on [[w:June 14]] [[w:1779]].<ref name="jonesbook1991">{{cite book | author=K. G. Jones | year=1991 | title=Messier's Nebulae and Star Clusters | edition= 2nd edition | publisher=Cambridge University Press | location=Cambridge | isbn=0-521-37079-5 }}</ref> The galaxy was then listed by [[w:Charles Messier]] as object 63 in the [[w:Messier Catalogue]].
In the mid-1800s, [[w:Lord Rosse]] identified spiral structure within the galaxy, making this one of the first galaxies in which such structure was identified.<ref name="jonesbook1991"/>
[[image:M63 3.6 8.0 24 microns spitzer.png|thumb|left|Messier 63 seen in infrared by the [[w:Spitzer Space Telescope]].]]
<br style="clear:left;"/> ==External links== * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m063.html Sunflower Galaxy @ SEDS Messier pages]
