{{Infobox galaxy | image = [[w:File:Messier84a.jpg|200px]] | caption = ''M84''. Credit:[[w:NOAO]]. | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 84 | type = E1<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 4374 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-11-14}}</ref> | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | ra = {{RA|12|25|03.7}}<ref name="ned" /> | dec = {{DEC|+12|53|13}}<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = [[w:1 E23 m|60 ± 3]] [[w:light-year|Mly]] (18.4 ± 0.9 [[w:parsec|Mpc]])<ref name="tonryetal2001">{{cite journal | author=J. L. Tonry, A. Dressler, J. P. Blakeslee, E. A. Ajhar, A. B. Fletcher, G. A. Luppino, M. R. Metzger, C. B. Moore | title=The SBF Survey of Galaxy Distances. IV. SBF Magnitudes, Colors, and Distances | journal=Astrophysical Journal | year=2001 | volume=546 | issue=2 | pages=681–693 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2001ApJ...546..681T | doi=10.1086/318301 }}</ref> | z = 1060 ± 6 km/[[w:second|s]]<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 10.1<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 6&prime;.5 &times; 5&prime;.6<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]] | notes = - | names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4374,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 7494,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 40455,<ref name="ned" /> VCC 763<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''Messier 84''' (also known as ''M84'' or ''NGC 4374'') is a [[w:lenticular galaxy]] in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]]. M84 is situated in the heavily populated inner core of the [[w:Virgo Cluster|Virgo Cluster of galaxies]].<ref name="Finoguenovetal2002">{{cite journal | author=Finoguenov, A.; Jones, C. | title=Chandra Observation of Low-Mass X-Ray Binaries in the Elliptical Galaxy M84 | journal=The Astrophysical Journal | year=2002 | volume=574 | issue=2 | pages=754–761 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=2002ApJ...574..754F | doi=10.1086/340997 }}</ref>
Radio observations and images of the [[w:Hubble Space Telescope]] of M84 have revealed two jets of matter shooting out from the galaxy's center as well as a disk of rapidly rotating gas and stars close to the nucleus indicating the presence of a supermassive [[w:black hole]] of 18 {{e|8}} [[w:solar mass|M<sub>☉</sub>]]<ref name="Lyetal2004">{{cite journal | author=Ly, C.; Walker, R. C.; Wrobel, J. M. | title=An Attempt to Probe the Radio Jet Collimation Regions in NGC 4278, NGC 4374 (M84), and NGC 6166 | journal=The Astronomical Journal | year=2004 | volume=127 | issue=1 | pages=119–124 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=2004AJ....127..119L | doi=10.1086/379855 }}</ref> in the galaxy's nucleus.
[[image:Messier 84 nucleus Hubble.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Messier 84 nucleus by [[w:Hubble Space Telescope|HST]]]]
==History== [[w:Charles Messier]] discovered Messier 84 on 18 March 1781 in a systematic search for "nebulous objects" in the night sky<ref name="jonesbook1991">{{cite book | author=K. G. Jones | year=1991 | title=Messier's Nebulae and Star Clusters | edition= 2nd | publisher=Cambridge University Press | location=Cambridge | isbn=0-521-37079-5 }}</ref>. The object is the 84th in the [[w:Messier Catalogue]].
==Supernovae== Two [[w:supernova]]e have been observed in M84: [[w:SN 1957]]<ref name="Götz1958">{{cite journal | author=Götz, W. | title=Supernova in NGC 4374 (= M 84) | journal=Astronomische Nachrichten | year=1958 | volume=284 | pages=141 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1958AN....284..141G | doi=10.1002/asna.19572840308 }}</ref> and [[w:SN 1991bg]].<ref name="Kosaietal1991">{{cite journal | author=Kosai, H.; Kushida, R.; Kato, T.; Filippenko, A.; Newberg, H. | title=Supernova 1991bg in NGC 4374 | journal=IAU Circ. | year=1958 | volume=5400 | pages=1 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1991IAUC.5400....1K }}</ref> Possibly, a third, [[w:SN 1980I]] is part of M84 or, alternatively, one of its neighboring galaxies, [[w:NGC 4387]] and [[w:Messier 86|M86]].<ref name="Smith1981">{{cite journal | author=Smith, H. A. | title=The spectrum of the intergalactic supernova 1980I | journal=Astronomical Journal | month=July | year=1981 | volume=86 | pages=998–1002 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1981AJ.....86..998S | doi=10.1086/112975 }}</ref>
==External links== * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m084.html SEDS Lenticular Galaxy M84]
