{{Infobox galaxy | image = [[image:M85.jpg|244px]] | caption = M85, courtesy of [[w:NOAO]] | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 85 | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | type = SA(s)0 pec<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for Messier 85 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-11-18 }}</ref> | ra = {{RA|12|25|24.0}}<ref name="ned" /> | dec = {{DEC|+18|11|28}}<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = [[w:1 E23 m|60 ± 4]] [[w:light-year|Mly]] (18.5 ± 1.2 [[w:parsec|Mpc]])<ref name="tonryetal2001">{{cite journal | author=J. L. Tonry, A. Dressler, J. P. Blakeslee, E. A. Ajhar, A. B. Fletcher, G. A. Luppino, M. R. Metzger, C. B. Moore | title=The SBF Survey of Galaxy Distances. IV. SBF Magnitudes, Colors, and Distances | journal=Astrophysical Journal | year=2001 | volume=546 | issue=2 | pages=681–693 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2001ApJ...546..681T | doi=10.1086/318301 }}</ref> | z = 729 ± 2 [[w:kilometer|km]]/[[w:second|s]]<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 10.0<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 7&prime;.1 &times; 5&prime;.5<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[w:Coma Berenices]] | notes = | names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4382, [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 7508, [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 40515<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''Messier 85''' (also known as '''M85''' or '''NGC 4382''') is a [[w:lenticular galaxy]] (type S0) in the [[w:Coma Berenices constellation]]. It is 60 million light years away, making it the 94th most distant Messier object, and it estimated to be 125,000 light years across.
It was discovered by [[w:Pierre Méchain]] in [[w:1781]]. It is the northernmost outlier of the [[w:Virgo cluster]] discovered as of 2004.
The type I [[w:supernova]], [[w:1960R]] was discovered in M85 on Dec 20, [[w:1960]] and reached an [[w:apparent magnitude]] of 11.7.
M85 is interacting with the nearby [[w:spiral galaxy]] [[w:NGC 4394]], and a small [[w:elliptical galaxy]] called [[w:MCG 3-32-38]]<ref name="kopernik">{{cite web | title=M85, Lenticular Galaxy | work=Messier's Nebulae and Star Clusters | url=http://www.kopernik.org/images/archive/m85.htm | accessdate=2009-03-29 }}</ref>.
== External links == * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m085.html SEDS Lenticular Galaxy M85]
