{{Infobox galaxy | image = | caption = | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 86 | type = S0(3)/E3<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 4406 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-11-14}}</ref> | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | ra = {{RA|12|26|11.7}}<ref name="ned" /> | dec = {{DEC|+12|56|46}}<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = [[w:1 E23 m|52 ± 3]] [[w:light-year|Mly]] (15.9 ± 1.0 [[w:parsec|Mpc]])<ref name="jensenetal2003">{{cite journal | author=Jensen, Joseph B.; Tonry, John L.; Barris, Brian J.; Thompson, Rodger I.; Liu, Michael C.; Rieke, Marcia J.; Ajhar, Edward A.; Blakeslee, John P. | title=Measuring Distances and Probing the Unresolved Stellar Populations of Galaxies Using Infrared Surface Brightness Fluctuations | journal=Astrophysical Journal | month=February | year=2003 | volume=583 | issue=2 | pages=712–726 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2003ApJ...583..712J | doi=10.1086/345430 }}</ref> | z = -0.000814 +/- 0.000017 (-244 ± 5 km/[[w:second|s]])<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 9.8<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 8&prime;.9 &times; 5&prime;.8<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]] | notes = displays a rare [[w:blue shift]] | names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4406,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 7532,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 40653,<ref name="ned" /> VCC 0881<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''Messier 86''' (also known as '''M86''' or '''NGC 4406''') is a [[w:lenticular galaxy]] in the constellation [[w:Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]]. It was discovered by [[w:Charles Messier]] in [[w:1781]]. M86 lies in the heart of the [[w:Virgo Cluster|Virgo Cluster of galaxies]] and forms a most conspicuous group with another giant, [[w:Lenticular Galaxy M84]]. It displays the highest [[w:blue shift]] of all Messier objects, as it is approaching the [[w:Milky Way]] at 244 km/s. This is thought to be due to its falling towards the center of the Virgo cluster, which brings it closer to us.<ref name="Jacobyetal2005">{{cite journal | author=Jacoby, G. H.; Kenney, J. D. P.; Tal, T.; Crowl, H. H.; Feldmeier, J. J. | title=Imaging and Spectroscopy of Large Scale H-alpha Filaments in M86 | journal=American Astronomical Society Meeting 207, #138.06; Bulletin of the American Astronomical Society | year=2005 | volume=37 | pages=1392 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=2005AAS...20713806J }}</ref>
==External links== * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m086.html SEDS Lenticular Galaxy M86]
