'''Messier 88''' (also known as ''M88'' or ''NGC 4501'') is a [[w:spiral galaxy]] about [[w:1 E23 m|47 million]] [[w:light-year]]s away in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Coma Berenices]]. The galaxy is a member of the [[w:Virgo Cluster]]. It was discovered by [[w:Charles Messier]] in [[w:1781]].
