{{Infobox galaxy | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 91 | image = [[File:Messier91.jpg]] |caption = Spiral Galaxy M91. Atlas Image courtesy of 2MASS/UMass/IPAC-Caltech/NASA/NSF. | epoch = [[w:J2000|J2000]] | type = SBb(rs)<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 4548 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2006-12-13 }}</ref> | ra = {{RA|12|35|26.4}}<ref name="ned" /> | dec = {{DEC|+14|29|47}}<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly = [[w:1 E23 m|63 ± 16]] [[w:light-year|Mly]] (19 ± 5 [[w:parsec|Mpc]])<ref name="tonryetal2001">{{cite journal | author=J. L. Tonry, A. Dressler, J. P. Blakeslee, E. A. Ajhar, A. B. Fletcher, G. A. Luppino, M. R. Metzger, C. B. Moore | title=The SBF Survey of Galaxy Distances. IV. SBF Magnitudes, Colors, and Distances | journal=Astrophysical Journal | year=2001 | volume=546 | issue=2 | pages=681–693 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2001ApJ...546..681T | doi=10.1086/318301 }}</ref> | z = 486 ± 4 km/[[w:second|s]]<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 11.0<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 5&prime;.4 &times; 4&prime;.3<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[w:Coma Berenices|Coma Berenices]] | notes = | names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 4548,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 7753,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 41934<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''Messier 91''' (also known as ''NGC 4548'') is a [[w:barred spiral galaxy|barred spiral galaxy]] about [[w:1 E23 m|63 million]] [[w:light-year|light-year]]s away in the [[w:constellation|constellation]] [[w:Coma Berenices|Coma Berenices]]. It was most probably discovered by [[w:Charles Messier|Charles Messier]] in [[w:1781|1781]] and independently rediscovered by [[w:William Herschel|William Herschel]] on [[w:April 8|April 8]], [[w:1784|1784]]. M91 is a member of the [[w:Virgo cluster|Virgo Cluster of galaxies]].
==External links== * [http://www.seds.org/messier/m/m091.html SEDS Messier: Spiral Galaxy M91]
