{{Infobox galaxy | name = [[w:Messier object|Messier]] 95 | image = [[image:Messier95 spitzer.jpg|350px]] | caption = M95. Credit: [[w:NASA]] | epoch = [[w:J2000]] | ra = {{RA|10|43|57.7}}<ref name="ned">{{cite web | title=NASA/IPAC Extragalactic Database | work=Results for NGC 3351 | url=http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/ | accessdate=2007-10-03}}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|+11|42|14}}<ref name="ned" /> | constellation name = [[w:Leo (constellation)|Leo]] | z = 778 ± 4 km/[[w:second|s]]<ref name="ned" /> | dist_ly =[[w:1 E23 m|32.6 ± 1.4]] [[w:light-year|Mly]] (10.0 ± 0.4 [[w:parsec|Mpc]])<ref name="jensenetal2003">{{cite journal | author=Jensen, Joseph B.; Tonry, John L.; Barris, Brian J.; Thompson, Rodger I.; Liu, Michael C.; Rieke, Marcia J.; Ajhar, Edward A.; Blakeslee, John P. | title=Measuring Distances and Probing the Unresolved Stellar Populations of Galaxies Using Infrared Surface Brightness Fluctuations | journal=Astrophysical Journal | month=February | year=2003 | volume=583 | issue=2 | pages=712–726 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2003ApJ...583..712J | doi=10.1086/345430 }}</ref> | type = SB(r)b<ref name="ned" /> | appmag_v = 11.4<ref name="ned" /> | size_v = 3&prime;.1 &times; 2&prime;.9<ref name="ned" /> | notes = | names = [[w:New General Catalogue|NGC]] 3351,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Uppsala General Catalogue|UGC]] 5850,<ref name="ned" /> [[w:Principal Galaxies Catalogue|PGC]] 32007<ref name="ned" /> }}
'''Messier 95''' (also known as ''M95'' or ''NGC 3351'') is a [[w:barred spiral galaxy]] about [[w:1 E23 m|33 million]] [[w:light-year]]s away in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Leo (constellation)|Leo]]. It was discovered by [[w:Pierre Méchain]] in [[w:1781]], and catalogued by [[w:Charles Messier]] four days later.
==Nucleus== The center of the galaxy contains a ring-shaped circumnuclear star-forming region with a diameter of approximately 2000 [[w:light year|ly]] (600 [[w:parsec|pc]]).<ref>{{cite journal | author=L. Colina, M. L. Garcia Vargas, J. M. Mas-Hesse, A. Alberdi, A. Krabbe | title=Nuclear Star-forming Structures and the Starburst–Active Galactic Nucleus Connection in Barred Spirals NGC 3351 and NGC 4303 | journal=The Astrophysical Journal Letters | year=1997 | volume=484 | pages=L41–L45 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1997ApJ...484L..41C | doi=10.1086/310766 }}</ref>
==Galaxy group information== M95 is one of several galaxies within the [[w:M96 Group]], a [[w:group of galaxies]] in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Leo (constellation)|Leo]]. The group also includes the [[w:Messier objects]] [[w:Messier 96|M96]] and [[w:Messier 105|M105]].<ref name="nbg">{{cite book | author=R. B. Tully | year=1988 | title=Nearby Galaxies Catalog | edition= | publisher=Cambridge University Press | location=Cambridge | isbn=0-521-35299-1}}</ref><ref name="fouqueetal1992">{{cite journal | author=P. Fouque, E. Gourgoulhon, P. Chamaraux, G. Paturel | title=Groups of galaxies within 80 Mpc. II - The catalogue of groups and group members | journal=Astronomy and Astrophysics Supplement | year=1992 | volume=93 | pages=211–233 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1992A&AS...93..211F}}</ref><ref name="garcia1993">{{cite journal | author=A. Garcia | title=General study of group membership. II - Determination of nearby groups | journal=Astronomy and Astrophysics Supplement | year=1993 | volume=100 | pages=47–90 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1993A&AS..100...47G}}</ref><ref name="giuricinetal2002">{{cite journal | author=G. Giuricin, C. Marinoni, L. Ceriani, A. Pisani | title=Nearby Optical Galaxies: Selection of the Sample and Identification of Groups | journal=Astrophysical Journal | year=2000 | volume=543 | pages=178–194 | url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2000ApJ...543..178G | doi=10.1086/317070 }}</ref>
