{{ Cluster | | name = NGC 581 | image = [[image:Messier object 103.jpg|250px]] | epoch = J2000.0 | class = d | ra = 01<sup>h</sup>&nbsp;33.2<sup>m</sup> | dec = +60° 42&prime; | dist_ly = 8.5 [[w:light year|kly]] | dist_pc = | appmag_v = 7.4 | size_v = 6.0' | mass_kg = | mass_msol = - | radius_ly = | v_hb = - | age = | notes = | names = M103 }} '''Messier 103''' (also known as M103, or NGC 581) is an [[w:open cluster]] in the [[w:constellation]] [[w:Cassiopeia (constellation)|Cassiopeia]]. It was discovered by [[w:Pierre Méchain]] in [[w:1781]]{{Fact|date=March 2007}}. M103 is at a distance of about 8,000 [[w:light-year]]s from [[w:Earth]].
